    {
      "id": "note-1",
      "title": "MindSync Architecture Design",
      "content": "MindSync AI uses a pure Node.js HTTP server. It runs completely local-first with zero dependencies. The agent framework features seven distinct agents working on a shared database state (db.json). Tool use is supported through direct Gemini API calls and JSON-RPC Model Context Protocol (MCP). Make sure to implement rate limiting and request sanitization on all API routes.",
      "summary": "MindSync AI is built on a zero-dependency, local-first Node.js architecture. It coordinates seven autonomous agents using a shared JSON database state. Communication is handled via local HTTP routes and standard Model Context Protocol over stdio.",
      "tags": [
        "architecture",
        "nodejs",
        "agents",
        "mcp",
        "security"
      ],
      "actionItems": [
        "Implement rate limiting on all API routes",
        "Add input sanitization for note creation",
        "Configure MCP server for stdio protocol"
      ],
