    {
      "id": "note-2",
      "title": "Agentic AI Design Patterns",
      "content": "Modern agentic systems rely on orchestration, tool access, and dynamic routing. Instead of a single large model prompt, specialized sub-agents perform individual tasks such as ingestion, web clipping, conflict detection, and concept generation. Agents must communicate structured outputs, often using JSON formats. Security guards should wrap all agent tool executions to prevent prompt injection and unauthorized command execution.",
      "summary": "Specialized sub-agents are preferred over single monolithic prompts in agentic design patterns. Agents coordinate tasks through structured JSON communication and tool access. Input verification and execution guards are vital security components.",
      "tags": [
        "agents",
        "design-patterns",
        "ai",
        "security"
      ],
      "actionItems": [
        "Create tool access wrapper for Chat Agent",
        "Setup prompt injection validation guidelines"
      ],
      "embedding": [
